properties.name: caller
properties.description:
Use the non-standard {@see Function.prototype.caller} property of a function
object instead.

functions.name: constructor
functions.description: The constructor of the current object.

functions.name: __defineGetter__
functions.description:
Binds an object's property to a function to be called when that property is
looked up.
Mozilla-only.

functions.name: __defineSetter__
functions.description:
Binds an object's property to a function to be called when an attempt is made
to set that property.
Mozilla-only.

functions.name: hasOwnProperty
functions.description: Returns whether the object has a property with the specified name.

functions.name: isPrototypeOf
functions.description: Returns whether an object exists in another object's prototype chain.

functions.name: __lookupGetter__
functions.description:
Return the function bound as a getter to the specified property.
Mozilla-only.

parameters.name: sprop
parameters.description:
a string containing the name of the property whose
getter should be returned

functions.name: __lookupSetter__
functions.description:
Return the function bound as a setter to the specified property.
Mozilla-only.

parameters.name: sprop
parameters.description:
a string containing the name of the property whose
    setter should be returned.

functions.name: __noSuchMethod__
functions.description:
Executes a function when a non-existent method is called on an object.
Mozilla-only.

functions.name: propertyIsEnumerable
functions.description:
Determine whether the specified property in an object can be enumerated by a
for..in loop, with the exception of properties inherited through the
prototype chain.

functions.name: toLocaleString
functions.description: Returns a localized string representing the object.

functions.name: toSource
functions.description:
Returns a string representing the source code of the object.
Mozilla-only.

functions.name: toString
functions.description: Returns a string representing the object.

functions.name: valueOf
functions.description: Returns the object's `this` value.

properties.name: __parent__
properties.description:
Points to an object's context.  For top-level objects, this is the e.g. window.
Mozilla-only.

properties.name: __proto__
properties.description:
Points to the object which was used as prototype when the object was instantiated.
Mozilla-only.

Will be null on Object.prototype.

functions.name: concat
functions.description:
Returns a new array comprised of this array joined with other array(s)
and/or value(s).

functions.name: join
functions.description: Joins all elements of an array into a string.

parameters.name: opt_separator
parameters.description:
Specifies a string to separate each element of the
    array. The separator is converted to a string if necessary. If omitted,
    the array elements are separated with a comma.

functions.name: pop
functions.description: Removes the last element from an array and returns that element.

functions.name: push
functions.description:
Mutates an array by appending the given elements and returning the new
length of the array.

returns.description: The new length of the array.

functions.name: reverse
functions.description:
Transposes the elements of an array in place: the first array element becomes the
last and the last becomes the first. The mutated array is also returned.

returns.description: A reference to the original modified array.

functions.name: shift
functions.description:
Removes the first element from an array and returns that element. This
method changes the length of the array.

functions.name: slice
functions.description: Extracts a section of an array and returns a new array.

parameters.name: opt_begin
parameters.description:
Zero-based index at which to begin extraction.  A
    non-number type will be auto-cast by the browser to a number.

parameters.name: opt_end
parameters.description:
Zero-based index at which to end extraction.  slice
    extracts up to but not including end.

functions.name: sort
functions.description: Sorts the elements of an array in place.

parameters.name: opt_compareFn
parameters.description:
Specifies a function that
    defines the sort order.

functions.name: splice
functions.description:
Changes the content of an array, adding new elements while removing old
elements.

parameters.name: opt_index
parameters.description:
Index at which to start changing the array. If negative,
    will begin that many elements from the end.  A non-number type will be
    auto-cast by the browser to a number.

parameters.name: opt_howMany
parameters.description:
An integer indicating the number of old array elements
    to remove.

functions.name: unshift
functions.description:
Adds one or more elements to the beginning of an array and returns the new
length of the array.

returns.description: The new length of the array

functions.name: reduce
functions.description:
Apply a function simultaneously against two values of the array (from
left-to-right) as to reduce it to a single value.

functions.name: reduceRight
functions.description:
Apply a function simultaneously against two values of the array (from
right-to-left) as to reduce it to a single value.

functions.name: every
functions.description: Available in ECMAScript 5, Mozilla 1.6+.

functions.name: filter
functions.description: Available in ECMAScript 5, Mozilla 1.6+.

functions.name: forEach
functions.description: Available in ECMAScript 5, Mozilla 1.6+.

functions.name: indexOf
functions.description: Available in ECMAScript 5, Mozilla 1.6+.

functions.name: lastIndexOf
functions.description: Available in ECMAScript 5, Mozilla 1.6+.

functions.name: map
functions.description: Available in ECMAScript 5, Mozilla 1.6+.

functions.name: some
functions.description: Available in ECMAScript 5, Mozilla 1.6+.

functions.name: indexOf
functions.description: Mozilla 1.6+ only.

functions.name: lastIndexOf
functions.description: Mozilla 1.6+ only.

functions.name: isArray
functions.description: Introduced in 1.8.5.

functions.name: toString
functions.description: Returns a string representing the number.

functions.name: parse
functions.description:
Parses a string representation of a date, and returns the number
of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00, local time.

functions.name: setDate
functions.description: Sets the day of the month for a specified date according to local time.

functions.name: setMonth
functions.description: Set the month for a specified date according to local time.

functions.name: setFullYear
functions.description: Sets the full year for a specified date according to local time.

functions.name: setYear
functions.description: Sets the year for a specified date according to local time.

functions.name: setHours
functions.description: Sets the hours for a specified date according to local time.

functions.name: setMinutes
functions.description: Sets the minutes for a specified date according to local time.

functions.name: setSeconds
functions.description: Sets the seconds for a specified date according to local time.

functions.name: setMilliseconds
functions.description: Sets the milliseconds for a specified date according to local time.

functions.name: setTime
functions.description:
Sets the Date object to the time represented by a number of milliseconds
since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.

functions.name: setUTCDate
functions.description: Sets the day of the month for a specified date according to universal time.

functions.name: setUTCMonth
functions.description: Sets the month for a specified date according to universal time.

functions.name: setUTCFullYear
functions.description: Sets the full year for a specified date according to universal time.

functions.name: setUTCHours
functions.description: Sets the hour for a specified date according to universal time.

functions.name: setUTCMinutes
functions.description: Sets the minutes for a specified date according to universal time.

functions.name: setUTCSeconds
functions.description: Sets the seconds for a specified date according to universal time.

functions.name: setUTCMilliseconds
functions.description: Sets the milliseconds for a specified date according to universal time.

functions.name: charAt
functions.description: Returns the specified character from a string.

functions.name: charCodeAt
functions.description:
Returns a number indicating the Unicode value of the character at the given
index.

functions.name: concat
functions.description: Combines the text of two or more strings and returns a new string.

functions.name: indexOf
functions.description:
Returns the index within the calling String object of the first occurrence
of the specified value, starting the search at fromIndex, returns -1 if the
value is not found.

functions.name: lastIndexOf
functions.description:
Returns the index within the calling String object of the last occurrence of
the specified value, or -1 if not found. The calling string is searched
backward, starting at fromIndex.

functions.name: localeCompare
functions.description:
Returns a number indicating whether a reference string comes before or after
or is the same as the given string in sort order.

functions.name: match
functions.description:
Used to retrieve the matches when matching a string against a regular
expression.

returns.description:
This should really return an Array with a few
    special properties, but we do not have a good way to model this in
    our type system. Also see Regexp.prototype.exec.

functions.name: replace
functions.description:
Finds a match between a regular expression and a string, and replaces the
matched substring with a new substring.

This may have side-effects if the replacement function has side-effects.

functions.name: search
functions.description:
Executes the search for a match between a regular expression and this String
object.

properties.name: input
properties.description: The string against which the last regexp was matched.

properties.name: lastParen
properties.description: The last matched parenthesized substring, if any.

properties.name: leftContext
properties.description: The substring of the input up to the characters most recently matched.

properties.name: rightContext
properties.description: The substring of the input after the characters most recently matched.

properties.name: global
properties.description:
Whether to test the regular expression against all possible matches
in a string, or only against the first.

properties.name: ignoreCase
properties.description: Whether to ignore case while attempting a match in a string.

properties.name: lastIndex
properties.description: The index at which to start the next match.

properties.name: sticky
properties.description: Whether or not the regular expression uses lastIndex.

properties.name: multiline
properties.description: Whether or not to search in strings across multiple lines.

properties.name: flags
properties.description: The flags the regex was created with.

properties.name: groups
properties.description:
Not actually part of ES3; was added in 2018.
https://github.com/tc39/proposal-regexp-named-groups

properties.name: stackTraceLimit
properties.description:
Chrome/v8 specific, altering the maximum depth of the stack trace
(10 by default).

properties.name: sourceURL
properties.description: Doesn't seem to exist, but closure/debug.js references it.

functions.name: captureStackTrace
functions.description:
Chrome/v8 specific, adds a stack trace to the error object. The optional
constructorOpt parameter allows you to pass in a function value. When
collecting the stack trace all frames above the topmost call to this
function, including that call, will be left out of the stack trace.

parameters.name: error
parameters.description: The object to add the stack trace to.

parameters.name: opt_constructor
parameters.description: A function in the stack trace

functions.name: escape
functions.description:
Should only be used in browsers where encode/decodeURIComponent
are not present, as the latter handle fancy Unicode characters.

functions.name: unescape
functions.description:
Should only be used in browsers where encode/decodeURIComponent
are not present, as the latter handle fancy Unicode characters.

functions.name: parseInt
functions.description:
Parse an integer. Use of `parseInt` without `base` is strictly
banned in Google. If you really want to parse octal or hex based on the
leader, then pass `undefined` as the base.
